stories_text_raw:
Here are the user stories derived from the Python code:

As a system administrator, I want to process 2017 data deletions, so that outdated submissions are removed from the database.

As a data manager, I want to update FABS submission status, so that I can track publication workflow and prevent duplicate publishing.

As a validation specialist, I want to update validation rules, so that data quality checks remain current with business requirements.

As a data analyst, I want to generate D files with caching, so that I can efficiently access combined FABS/FPDS data with minimal processing.

As a UI designer, I want to track UI change requests with version rounds, so that design iterations are properly documented.

As a QA tester, I want to schedule user testing sessions, so that we can validate system usability with proper test scenarios.

As a data engineer, I want to load historical FABS data with derived fields, so that we maintain a complete dataset with enhanced information.

As a system administrator, I want to configure New Relic monitoring, so that application performance is continuously tracked.

As an API user, I want to publish FABS submissions via API, so that I can automate the publication workflow.

As a UI team member, I want to submit UI change requests via API, so that modifications are systematically recorded.

As a testing coordinator, I want to schedule user tests via API, so that session management is integrated with our systems.

As a data consumer, I want to retrieve generated D files via API, so that I can access current agency data on demand.

As a data archivist, I want to load historical FABS data via API, so that we can systematically backfill our database.
